WorkItem.Description:
Can anyone point me to a good aggregation example?
 
In particular, I want to go from a flat structure, to a modified deep structure.  All the projection examples deep with deep structures to flat structures.
 
In this case, given a list of PricingItem objects, I want a list of ViewCategories with multiple ViewItems under it.  It's an aggregation/coalation problem. 
 
Say I have a source PricingItem class that looks like this:
 
public class PricingItem
    {
        public int Id { get; set; }
        public CategoryType Category { get; set; }
        public int Value { get; set; }
    }
 
And I have an associated ViewCategory that is an aggegation by CategoryType as determined by the source PricingItem.
 
    public class ViewCategory
    {
        public CategoryType Category { get; set; }
        public IEnumerable<ViewItem> ViewItems { get; set; }
    }
 
    public class ViewItem
    {
        public int Id { get; set; }
        public int Value { get; set; }
    }
 
Thank you,
-Steve
